BUILT TO PERFORM RAIN OR SHINE

You never know where the hunt will take you, which is why Thompson/Center adopted its innovative Weather Shield® coating to endure the elements. ACCURACY YOU CAN COUNT ON WITH AN MOA GUARANTEE

Out of the box, T/C Venture rifles are equipped with a minute of angle guarantee, meaning it will shoot a 3 shot group in an inch or less at 100 yards (with premium ammunition). 5R RIFLING LEADS TO A BETTER SHOT

Different from conventional 6-groove rifling, 5R rifling results in less deformation of the bullet jacket and a better gas seal. It causes less bullet upset and less barrel fouling, leading to a cleaner shot that you can count on hunt after hunt, year after year, with easier cleaning.

GET A GRIP ON HUNTING

Your heart is racing, your palms are sweaty, but your head is cool. With Hogue raised traction panels on the T/C Venture, you don’t have to worry about missing the perfect shot. These innovative raised grips provide the stability needed to keep you on target in any weather conditions.

The standard serrated trigger can cause point of impact drift when the trigger finger drags across the trigger face. Pearce grip extensions for better control while not giving up conceal ability . Titanium alloy assembly pins and take down that are drift, wear, and corrosion resistant. Vickers extended and contoured mag release and Glock extended slide release. All original factory parts, paperwork, hardware, hardcase, Glock Holster and mag pouch, two 10 round magazines are included. This G30 is made in Austria with the dark black Tennifer finish that is proven to last longer then the newer grayish finish. This pistol has extremely light wear and only range use and looks new. The pistol has not had enough rounds fired in it to even break it in. I use this same setup in many other Glocks (21, 22,23,27,) and if works flawlessly and holds up perfectly, much better then out of the box.

Any upgrades can be un done. All factory parts are included.

Pistol fires extremely well. It has a crisp, light and clean break with tight groups. While it is outstanding I use the M&Ps and Rugers more which has left the G30 sitting in the safe.

May include up to 400 round 230 Winchester FMJ and up to 200 Defense rounds depending on trade. Also have additional G30 (10rd) and G21 (13 rd) magazines depending on trade. 

Email for more photos, questions, prices work ups. Pistol is NOT for sale.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1976 Ford F-100 Ranger XLT 4X4 Short Bed Truck
postcontent:
If this ad is up I do still have the truck for sale and thanks for your interest.

This is a really nice daily driver truck.  It has passed a Texas safety inspection and is licensed and insured.  The 4 wheel drive works as designed and has manual lock out hubs.

The best way to tell you about the truck is to break it down in sections. 

ENGINE
Back in November 2013 I had the engine removed for a professional rebuild.  Once the engine was removed I had the engine compartment stripped of all components.  The engine compartment was degreased, sandblasted, and repainted factory flat black.  All the components were degreased and repainted.  The 390 CI engine was totally dismantled.  It has new rings, pistons, heavy cam, springs, lifters, rods, Holley 4 barrel carb with electric choke, spark plugs, spark plug wires, distributor cap, coil harness, bearings and gaskets.  The heads and crank shaft were remanufactured and the block bored .30 over.  The block and intake were sandblasted and repainted Ford Corporate Blue like from the factory.  It has all these NEW parts;  aluminum radiator with transmission cooler, fan shroud, true headers, alternator, battery, voltage regulator, power steering pump, steering gear box, water pump, harmonic balancer, brake booster, master cylinder, air cleaner, oil pump, fluids, belts and hoses.  The exhaust/muffler is pretty new.  The Ford factory air works and blows cold and has been updated to the current R134 refrigerant.  It does need a new blower motor.  It needs a new windshield wiper fluid reservoir.   The fluid pump works fine.

STEERING, SUSPENSION, and BRAKES
The front end has been rebuilt with new polyurethane bushings on the track arm, idler arms, and C-bushings. The rear end has been rebuilt with new pinion seals, oil seals (inner and outer) differential fluid, and bearings on both wheels.   It has all these NEW parts; Skyjacker shocks, Skyjacker steering stabilizer, pitman arm, power steering pump, steering column shifter collar, master cylinder, brake booster, and brake shoes all around.  It has a new aftermarket steering wheel.  Could probably use new rear leaf spring shackle bushings and a new steering shaft in the future.

BODY AND WHEELS
This truck has spent its whole life in the arid temps of Texas.  It has all the original body panels and floor pans.  I did a VIN check and there has been no incidents reported of any collision or body repair.  I had it inspected at a body shop and they reported that they could find no body putty or rust repair.  It is a solid truck.  The paint is not original and it looks to be an older restoration maybe.  It is really shiny and damage free with the exception of a nic on the right front corner of the hood.  It does have some dings and couple of flakes on the hood.   All the chrome work appears to be present and is in nice shape.  It could use some polish.  I think the industry calls this a good “20 footer”.   The bed has been used but does have an older spray in liner that needs re-done.  It has a frame mounted receiver hitch that could be used to pull a boat or trailer (that is why it has the new transmission cooler).  I have never pulled anything with it.   The doors, hood and tailgate work as designed.  The glass is tinted.  It has a rear slider window.  Has new rubber door seals.  The windshield has a scratch on it from the windshield wiper.  The frame is straight.  The tires are TOYO 33x12.5X18 and are in decent shape.  The wheels are 18 Inch Eagle Series 197 Chrome.  They have recently been rotated and balanced.

ELECTRICAL
The electrical system has been inspected by an ASE mechanic and any problems corrected.  All the lights, gauges, switches, and wipers work as designed.  It has all these NEW parts: 36 month battery, alternator, voltage regulator, interior light bulbs, dash/gauge light bulbs, headlight switch, right tail light socket and bulb.  The original gauges were inoperable and replaced with a functional old stock set.

INTERIOR
The interior is really nice.  It has NEW carpet and seat belts.  The seat has probably been re-covered at some point.  It is black vinyl and in the correct style.  No rips, tears or soft spots.  The adjustment mechanism works great.  The stereo is a Sony CD player with detachable face, aux for IPod music, and remote.  It could use better speakers (door ones work).  The windows roll as designed.  The door handles work as designed.  The door skins are in really nice shape.   It does need a glove-box insert, headliner, dome light lens, left vent louver, and right wing window latch to finish it out. 

As you can see the truck is ready for another 100,000 miles.  Mechanically solid.  It is not a show truck and I wasn’t rebuilding it for that purpose.  I like driving it and wanted it to be a daily driver.  It gets a lot of looks and compliments.   It is after all a 38 year old truck.  Check out the NADA book values on this truck.  When you do just make sure you DON’T use the Custom model.  This truck is a F100 Short Bed Styleside with factory air, 4X4 and 390 engine.  The Ranger XLT trim package in a short bed is RARE.   I am located in Keller, Texas.  If you would like to come out and take a look let me know.  I can also help arrange shipping if you are interested.  If you have any other questions or need pictures of anything else let me know.  

I have A LOT invested in this truck and I am asking $17,000 but make me a cash offer and we can negotiate from there.  If you want to try to broker a trade for high end firearms I will listen.  NOTHING ELSE will be accepted for trade.

Semper Fi,

Tim

 A beautifull rifle reflecting a unique period in Australian shooting history, where many excess 303's were "sporterized" for Kangaroo and varmit shooting etc. The yanks may call it a Wildcat......you definitey won't find another like it.
